{
  "stem": "9701.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the begging by the children continued, because Germany was in pretty bad shape.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was then finally able to give children whatever they were asking for or whatever I had.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they had to eat it right in front of me, could not take it home, because at home there might be a Nazi.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And cigarettes, no, you're too young to smoke and you can't take them home.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the hatred across the board for the adult German population stayed with me for all too long.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I finally was able to rid myself of that hatred in the spring of 1970.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I-- at that time, the United States was involved in the Vietnam War.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I had been against that war probably before there was even an anti-Vietnam war movement.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I learned in late April or early May 1970 that as part of the Vietnam War, the United States had been carpet-bombing Cambodia.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And it-- I just was enraged that we had done this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But it also triggered some thoughts in my mind.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I was saying, you know, I picketed and I marched and I wrote letters and sent telegrams to my congressional people, to the president.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it didn't endanger my life or that of my family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then my thoughts traveled across the ocean and across the years back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I was saying, now, if the Germans had done what I did, they would have been sent to a concentration camp or there would have been some dire consequences for them.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And there was resistance in Germany, but most of those people unfortunately did not survive.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so I was saying, you know, how can I condemn a whole nation of people for not being heroes?",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
